# Tokfai architecture (must respect)

```
apps/
├── web/        # Vercel frontend  (tokfai.com)
└── dmit-api/   # Core backend     (api.tokfai.com)
supabase/       # DB migrations (source of truth)
```

## Layers

- **Supabase** — Auth + DB. Owns `auth.users`, `profiles`, `credit_ledger`,
  `usage_logs`, `api_keys` (hashed). Frontend uses anon key + RLS only.
- **`apps/web`** — `tokfai.com`. Marketing, auth UI, dashboard, Playground,
  Usage, Credits. Calls Supabase Auth + DMIT public API.
- **`apps/dmit-api`** — `api.tokfai.com`. OpenAI-compatible API, API-key auth,
  GRSAI calls, credit debiting, Stripe webhook. Holds all server-only secrets.

## Secret matrix

| Secret | Allowed in `apps/web` | Allowed in `apps/dmit-api` |
|---|---|---|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` | ✅ | — |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | ❌ never | ✅ |
| `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET` | ❌ never | ✅ |
| `TOKEN_PEPPER` | ❌ never | ✅ |
| `TOKFAI_KEY_ENCRYPTION_SECRET` | ❌ never | ✅ |
| `GRSAI_API_KEY` | ❌ never | ✅ |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | ❌ never | ✅ |
| `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | ❌ never | ✅ |

If a task asks you to put any DMIT-only secret into `apps/web`, stop and
push back — the logic belongs in DMIT instead.

See `AGENTS.md` for full detail.
